<br>
hope this helps... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 821<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 12:30:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: Ability to solo, where?</span><hr size=1> I can't say I successfully solo in any of the PoP zones, but at level 61 (and since 59 at the earliest) it has been possible for me to partner with practically ANY class and get experience in at least Tier 1 zones.<br>
<br>
I would imagine that once I get PoP level pets I could try the same in Tier 2 zones, though it would be just a little bit scarier.<br>
<br>
Ideally I want the 65 Earth pet, but perhaps with a regular &quot;distractor&quot; partner I could do just fine with the 61 Air. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valarionelementalist>Valarion Elementalist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 2:57:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   mana inefficient?</span><hr size=1> can´t really say that for a quadding wiz in PoV the exp is inefficient! Easy to get Kei / Virtue / potg or whatever buff you want in that zone and kiting 5 min. to get 2 blue AA (that´s prolly the minimum guess) and just med another 5 min. and tell the mage you just saw at zone in to toss you a rod isn´t really downtime... if you get trouble, just zone out (clicking a tombstone ain´t that hard) <br>
Only problems that wizzies might have is bad luck on resists, we have the nicer part there, malosinia, /pet attack, chainblast, no resists, repeat... med... but still, soloing is boring... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moozoo>moozoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 3:01:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mana inefficient?</span><hr size=1> First thing... not all wizards are equal, regardless of level.<br>
<br>
My wizard is lv 64, 19aa's FT1 and ~3990 mana and can just manage to solo a golem in PoV. I go very low on mana and have to med kite, root and nuke with my nuke stick.<br>
If a spider adds I have to run like mad (with Sow) and hope I have time to get gate off.<br>
My mana regen is such that I won't start a kite until both my havests are up. ie 8 - 10 min down time between kites.<br>
<br>
Another wizard I know is lv65, 200+ aa and has alot more mana/mana regen than me. She can Quad the Golems and has enough mana/manaregen to be able to Full speed kite and kill a spider add and finish the quad. ie Huge difference. I would say that uber wizards make up maybe 5% of the total post lv60 wizard population.<br>
<br>
Secondly try waiting at the PoV zone in. Wait until a Baron wizard zones in lfg and suggest to them that you duo golems/razorfeins.<br>
There are usually lots of wizards lfg in PoV (the none uber ones).<br>
Wizard snares and kites a single mob down to ~70%, mage sticks pet on it and nukes occasionally. The wizard should be able to hold aggro (if not suggest to the wiz that they throw in some PoP stun nukes).<br>
<br>
I believe the frogs in PoS can also be done this way but suspect there might be a lot more problems with adds.<br>
<br>
Moozoo Sorcerer Povar<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://users.bigpond.net.au/moozoo">users.bigpond.net.au/moozoo</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 514<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 7:19:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Kiting Storms/Valor with a Ranger Partner</span><hr size=1> Yikes, someone discovered my froggies! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
OK, here's what I do.<br>
<br>
Grab a ranger. Yes, a ranger. Make sure he has an extra long range bow (such as <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=10277">Bow of Doom</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->). The idea is that the ranger pulls the frogs near the graveyard with his bow and pulls him to you. He then snares the frog, uses his level 9 DoT Flame Lick to hold aggro, and you whip out your Servant of Marr (62 water) and proceed to kite backstab it down. With only the pet doing damage, it's a 5 minute kill. Throw in chaincasted Firebolt of Tallon, kill time is reduced to roughly 2 minutes. If the ranger knows his stuff you and your pet will almost never out-aggro him.<br>
<br>
So far we've managed to get the 4 frogs closest to the graveyard, and with some practice my ranger partner can successfully single pull all 4 frogs without adds. Respawn time is 20 minutes though, so be prepared to wait. If one of the humans adds on the frog, CoH the ranger. The frog will hold his position while the human returns to its spawn point (makes for easy pulling).<br>
<br>
Valor is even better. Same technique, only hunt the crystalline golems and anything else in that area.<br>
<br>
As long as your ranger (and your pet) survives each pull you will never have &quot;downtime&quot; per se. (Hint: a horse and a clicky nuke are highly recommended).<br>
<br>
Off the froggies we were getting an AA apiece roughly every 2~3 hours. Low risk but less exp than the Golems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=webdaddyfresh>webdaddy fresh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 8:00:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: Kiting Storms/Valor with a Ranger Partner</span><hr size=1> I recently tried this with a necro after the latest patch and all of the those travelers assisted on the frog pull.  He was dead before he could FD, as this was unexpected.  Now, we can do it if he pulls then either FDs or I coth and we peel.<br>
<br>
Something to keep in mind <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
